[Cite as 06/03/2003 Case Announcements, 2003-0hio-2802.j

CASE ANNOUNCEMENTS AND ADMINISTRATIVE ACTIONS

June 3, 2003

MOTION AND PROCEDURAL RULINGS

1985-0007. State v. Williams.

Cuyahoga App. No. 47853. By entry filed April 1, 2003, this court ordered that appellant’s sentence be *1428earned into execution on Tuesday, the 24th day of June, 2003. In order to facilitate this court’s timely consideration of any matters relating to the execution of appellant’s sentence,

IT IS ORDERED by the court that the Chief Justice may suspend application of any provisions of the Rules of Practice of the Supreme Court, including, but not limited to, the filing requirements imposed by S.Ct.Prac.R. XIV(1).

IT IS FURTHER ORDERED by the court that sendee of documents as inquired by S.CtPrac.R. XIV(2) shall be personal or by facsimile transmission.

IT IS FURTHER ORDERED by the court that counsel of record for the parties shall supply this court with a copy of any document relating to this matter that is filed in, or issued by, any other court in this state or any federal court, as well as any commutation, pardon, or warrant of reprieve issued by the Governor. A copy of the document shall be delivered to the Office of the Clerk as soon as possible, either personally or by facsimile transmission.
